            <h1>BMI Calculator</h1>

            <h2>How to use it?</h2>
            <p>
                The purpose of a BMI (Body Mass Index) calculator is to provide an indication of whether someone's
                weight is healthy in relation to their height. BMI is a measurement of body fat based on a person's
                weight and height, and it's commonly used as an assessment tool to screen for weight categories that may
                lead to health problems.<br><br>

                BMI is calculated by dividing a person's weight in kilograms by their height in meters squared (BMI =
                kg/mÂ²). The resulting number is then used to categorize individuals into different weight categories:

            <ul class="list">
                <li>
                    BMI less than 18.5 - Underweight

                </li>
                <li>
                    BMI between 18.5 and 24.9 - Normal weight

                </li>
                <li>
                    BMI between 25 and 29.9 - Overweight

                </li>
                <li>
                    BMI over 30 - Obese

                </li>

            </ul>

            BMI is not a perfect measurement of body fat, and it has some limitations. For example, it does not take
            into account the difference between muscle mass and fat, which can be an issue for athletes or
            bodybuilders. Additionally, other factors such as age, gender, and ethnicity may also influence BMI.

            </p>

            <form id="something">
                <label class="bmiLabel" for="weight">Weight (kg):</label>
                <input type="number" id="weight" name="weight" required>

                <label class="bmiLabel" for="height">Height (cm):</label>
                <input type="number" id="height" name="height" required>

                <button type="button" class="btn form_button" onclick="calculateBMI()">Calculate BMI</button>

                <div class="result" id="result"></div>

            </form>

            <script>
                function calculateBMI() {
                    let weight = document.getElementById("weight").value;
                    let height = document.getElementById("height").value / 100;
                    let bmi = weight / (height * height);
                    let resultDiv = document.getElementById("result");
                    resultDiv.innerHTML = "Your BMI is: " + bmi.toFixed(2);
                }
            </script>


